item.title: Need to know how to set my server online
item.dc:creator: @iTroll iTroll
item.description:
@iTroll wrote:

[quote=“pkakidjr1, post:3, topic:279132”][quote author=iTroll link=topic=368414.msg2790055#msg2790055 date=1242687699]

[quote author=pkakidjr1 link=topic=368414.msg2790047#msg2790047 date=1242687404]
All I need is a simple link explaining I got the portfowarding part down just how do I set my IP in the server folders?

Thanks for reading-
Nate.
[/quote]Press start - run - type cmd.exe then when a black box comes up in it type “ipconfig” then find your default gateway which is something like 192.168..* Now remember that and go to EasyRSC folder then server then src - org - rscdaemon - server - Server.java and open it with wordpad or notepad and search for “localhost” then type your default gateway.

Now go to EasyRSC folder client/and or distributed client. Open “settings.ini” for where it says “server=” type your ip which can be found on: http://www.whatismyip.com/ now compile server and your done, hope it helped! ;D
[/quote]Trying it right now if I could rep you I would.[/quote]I know you would
